⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Juan "Johnnie" Rico
node H1 · H1 · ⟦Juan "Johnnie" Rico:H1:5885d4⟧

WHO   — Juan "Johnnie" Rico, son of a wealthy Filipino-descended family who enlisted on a whim against his father's wishes — and was forged through boot camp and the Bug War into a Mobile Infantry officer and a citizen who had earned the franchise.
WHAT  — The narrator of Starship Troopers — a powered-armor trooper of the war against the Arachnids, whose coming-of-age is also Heinlein's argument that the vote must be paid for in voluntary service.
WHERE — From his father's house on Earth, through the brutal boot camp, to the drop-ships and contested worlds of the war against the Bugs.
WHY   — Because citizenship is a privilege bought with responsibility, not a birthright; because the species that will not defend itself does not deserve to survive; and because a man finds out who he is only under fire.
HOW   — By surviving Camp Currie under Sergeant Zim, dropping in powered armor with the Roughnecks, learning the moral calculus of History and Moral Philosophy, and finally leading his own men as Lieutenant Rico's Roughnecks.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Service guarantees citizenship — the franchise is earned, never given.

